FBIS4-3551 "drchi078_d_94001" FBIS-CHI-94-078 Daily Report 22 Apr 1994 Northeast Asia XINHUA Notes Hata's Nomination as Japan's Prime Minister XINHUA Notes Hata's Nomination as Japan's Prime Minister OW2204075694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0639 GMT 22 Apr 94 OW2204075694 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Tokyo, April 22 (XINHUA) -- Japan's ruling coalition today picked Foreign Minister Tsutomu Hata to succeed Morihiro Hosokawa as prime minister. The decision was made at a meeting here this afternoon of the coalition parties which agreed to present the 58-year-old Hata as their joint candidate in a parliamentary vote next Monday. Observers here believe that the veteran Hata is certain to win because of the coalition's majority in the decisive lower house.
